-- Chancellor Osborne Says There Will Be `Concrete Steps' to Secure Recovery
-- B y   T h o m a s   P e n n y
-- 2010-11-12T08:17:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/chancellor-osborne-says-there-will-be-concrete-steps-to-secure-recovery.html
 U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
George Osborne said there will be concrete steps to secure the
recovery as a result of the G-20 summit in Seoul.  “People are going to see some concrete steps taken both in
Britain’s interests and the world’s interests to secure the
global economic recovery,” Osborne said in an interview with
BBC Radio 4’s Today show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Penny in London at 
